annotationA: MIP26555p1; Transporter activity; retinal binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: transport
annotationB: Retinol-binding protein pinta; Retinoid-binding protein which shows highest affinity for all-trans retinol. Can also bind all-trans forms of retinoic acid and retinal, but has lower affinity for cis form retinoids. Required in retinal pigment cells for rhodopsin biosynthesis
